{\large Cameron Bracken and Charlie Sharpsteen \\ \today}\vspace{1cm}
\end{center}


The \pkg{pgfSweave} package provides capabilities for ``caching'' graphics generated with \pkg{Sweave}.  This document highlights the features and usage of \pkg{pgfSweave}.  Using \pkg{pgfSweave}, figure labels are converted to \LaTeX{} strings so not only do they match the style of the document but \LaTeX{} math symbols/equations can be put in labels.  \pkg{pgfSweave} provides a new driver for \pkg{Sweave} (\code{pgfSweaveDriver}) and new chunk options \code{pgf} and \code{external} on top of the \code{cache} option provided by \pkg{cacheSweave}.  This package is built upon \pkg{cacheSweave} and therefore also \pkg{Sweave}.  This document assumes familiarity with \pkg{Sweave}.  

We'll start first with an example to entice you.  The following code chunk used with \pkg{pgfSweave} will produce the graphic below.

